text:
Dear Vistara Management, 
@airvistara

Do you take tea or Coffee in the morning? Of Course, you all do.
I wanted to bring to your attention a recent experience I had on your UK581 flight at 5:30 AM. As someone who enjoys a cup of tea or coffee in the morning, I was quite surprised to find that these basic refreshments were not offered to passengers. It was even more surprising to see the cabin crew enjoying their tea or coffee, while politely informing passengers that such beverages were not available.
I understand that flights can have specific catering policies, but considering that breakfast is included in the ticket, the absence of tea or coffee seems rather disappointing. Additionally, the way this was communicated by the crew was quite unprofessional. When asked, they responded rudely, instructing passengers to simply take their seats without further explanation.
As a loyal passenger, I feel this situation does not reflect the high standards Vistara is known for. I hope you will look into this matter and ensure that such experiences are avoided in the future.
Thank you for your attention to this issue.

@DGCAIndia

@airvistara

@MoCA_GoI

@consaff

@airvistara

@makemytrip
 absolute fraud company, After rescheduling of my international flight, I was assured by airvistara I will be refunded the Delhi-Varanasi leg once I travel to Singapore leg. I will lodging this one with the consumer forum

My experience was not at all good on the following parameters:
1. Food & Beverages ( Quality, Quantity, Variety);
2. Leg space / room;
3. Width of Seats in the Economy class;
4. Baggage handling and time ( TAT ) for the luggage to get delivered at the conveyor belt;
5. In flight magazine articles" quality and selection of topics;
6. Music played during touch down

The overall experience in flying with Vistara Airline has been average.
Some of the things they need to improve upon are as follows:
1. Width of the Seats;
2. Leg Space / Room between two seats;
3. Quality and Quantity of the meals served;
4. Choice and variety of the beverages offered.
5. Baggage handling at the arrival airport as also the time taken to deliver the baggage at the conveyor belts.
6. Quality of articles in the in flight magazine.
7. Usage of the accumulated CV points. Access to lounge for Base CV points also.

New planes A319 or A320 with sharklets (probably Neo's). Business Class offers real 4 C-class seats (2-2) compared to the standard 3-3 seatings in ECO.
for 2:40 h flight they offer a small warm lunch, hot towels up front (as I could the towles were also offered at leat in the premium economy). this means they are having a 3 class plane. totally different to the European short and midrange flights,
Staff is friendly, airplane was clean (compared what you can experience at some other airlines) with new Newspapers being offered but also 2 different were already available at each seat. flight was fairly on time. looking forward to my flight back to delhi.
